==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redemptioner
<hw>Re*demp"tion*er</hw> <pr>(-?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who redeems himself, as from debt or servitude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Formerly, one who, wishing to emigrate from Europe
to America, sold his services for a stipulated time to pay the expenses
of his passage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redemptionist</ent>⟦br⟧
